You don't always need a second verb! "MÃ¶chten" is perfect for directly stating what you want to have, especially food and drinks.

Ich mÃ¶chte eine Cola. (I would like a Cola.)

Ich mÃ¶chte eine Pizza. (I would like a pizza.)

Ich mÃ¶chte Ã„pfel. (I would like apples.)



